  57: | scenario | m (gap) | 95% CI | Core v0 delivers | central delivers | winner |
  58: |---|---|---|---|---|---|
  59: | PRO-CENTRAL (central's declared full-favourable endpoint) | **−29.5%** | [−29.9, −29.1] | 68% of oracle | 98% | **central** |
  60: | NO-MYOPIA (harm-aware and otherwise-competent continuity bundle) | **+6.1%** | [5.8, 6.4] | 91% | 85% | ≈ parity |
  61: | PROBABLE (source-motivated reference) | **+46.6%** | [46.0, 47.4] | 91% | 45% | Core v0 |
  62: | PRO-DISTRIBUTED (favourable, moderate) | **+199.8%** | [197, 202] | 96% | −104% (destroys value) | Core v0 |
  63: 
  64: - **Level field (both ways):** the central has a genuine winning region — under its declared full-favourable endpoint (low
  65:   participation + competent, harm-aware central) it wins ~30% and delivers 98% of the oracle. Core v0 wins under the
  66:   probable reference. The story from D/O: Core v0 is fairly robust (68–96%); the central swings 45%→85%→98% (or −104%
  67:   when myopic + harmful) — it depends on whether it sees the anti-value AND on citizen participation.
  68: - **Continuity / reconciliation with the NO-GO:** in this sequential, path-dependent decomposition, `MYOPIA_OFF`
  69:   changes only `s_exp,b_H_C` and reduces the gap `+46.6% → +30.4%`, or 16.2 of the 40.5-point decline to `NO_MYOPIA`
  70:   (~40%). The further move to the harm-aware and otherwise-competent `NO_MYOPIA` bundle reduces it by 24.3 points
  71:   (~60%). `NO_MYOPIA` is the continuity anchor to the symmetry-gate near-parity regime; this is a qualitative
  72:   reconciliation hypothesis across different DGPs, not a reproduced limit.
